@RolandRedJack; OptiFine is included with the other mods, but if you want i can Up a version with it on vanilla than i can :)

Most ModLoader mods should work, as long as you install them correctly and they do not conflict on any other classes. otherwise, backup your minecraft.jar and do it trial and error- if it crashes it probably isn't going to work :P

Thanks :P

@FireflyZeroOne; it is the same as the paid version but you cannot play on legit online servers. You can still play on 'cracked' servers

@Darkinferno3; You can try assigning more memory, but it must be a pretty serious mod if it is using all 1GB of the allocated RAM (Default minecraft only really needs 256-512MB) (what graphics card have you got as memory is not necessarily RAM).
Run it with this from the run dialogue (Windows Key and R) java -Xmx1536m -Xms1536m -jar %APPDATA%\.minecraft\minecraftSL.jar If that does not work change the -Xmx1536m and the -Xms1536m to something larger.
It may fix the problem, but maybe you should try turning the render distance down?
